modules.description: Initializes a configuration object from a filename, loading and parsing its contents. Works with a record type containing application settings and parameters. Used to read environment-specific values such as database connections or API endpoints at startup.

Provides domain lookup and parsing operations, including querying WHOIS data and extracting domain names and extensions from strings. Works with configuration records, strings, and JSON data structures. Used to retrieve and analyze domain registration details from IP addresses.

Fetches and parses WHOIS data for domains using an API, returning structured details like domain registration dates, contact info, and name servers. Operates on domain names and API keys, producing typed records with specific fields. Used to validate domain ownership, track registration changes, and retrieve technical details for network diagnostics.

Loads configuration settings from a file, enabling dynamic adjustment of application parameters. Processes domain information by querying WHOIS data and extracting domain names and extensions from text. Supports operations on configuration records, strings, and JSON, allowing for flexible domain analysis and integration with external services. Example tasks include retrieving registration details for a domain or parsing a list of URLs to identify domain extensions.
